    "@value" : "measurement datum"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Examples of measurement data are the recoding of the weight of a mouse as {40,mass,\"grams\"}, the recording of an observation of the behavior of the mouse {,process,\"agitated\"}, the recording of the expression level of a gene as measured through the process of microarray experiment {3.4,luminosity,}."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000125"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
