    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000125"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "x is ubiquitously expressed in y if and only if x is expressed in y, and the majority of cells in y express x"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116" : [ {
    "@value" : "Revisit this term after coordinating with SO/SOM. The domain of this relation should be a sequence, as an instance of a DNA molecule is only expressed in the cell of which it is a part."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002292",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000125"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "y expresses x if and only if there is a gene expression process (GO:0010467) that occurs in y, and one of the following holds: (i) x is a gene, and x is transcribed into a transcript as part of the gene expression process (ii) x is a transcript, and x was transcribed from a gene as part of the gene expression process (iii) x is a mature gene product (protein or RNA), and x was translated or otherwise processed from a transcript that was transcribed as part of the gene expression process."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002293",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000125"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "inverse of ubiquiotously expressed in"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002295",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000125"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "p results in the developmental progression of s iff p is a developmental process and s is an anatomical entity and p causes s to undergo a change in state at some point along its natural developmental cycle (this cycle starts with its formation, through the mature structure, and ends with its loss)."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116" : [ {
    "@value" : "This property and its subproperties are being used primarily for the definition of GO developmental processes. The property hierarchy mirrors the core GO hierarchy. In future we may be able to make do with a more minimal set of properties, but due to the way GO is currently structured we require highly specific relations to avoid incorrect entailments. To avoid this, the corresponding genus terms in GO should be declared mutually disjoint."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002296",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "every flower development (GO:0009908) results in development of some flower (PO:0009046)"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000114" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000125"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "p 'results in development of' c if and only if p is a developmental process and p results in the state of c changing from its initial state as a primordium or anlage through its mature state and to its final state."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165"
  } ],
