    "@value" : "treats"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/causal-relations"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002600",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112" : [ {
    "@value" : "benzene -> cancer [CHEBI]"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "Holds between a material entity c and a pathological process p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, where a negatively regulates p."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000118" : [ {
    "@value" : "causes disease"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/causal-relations"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002601",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "A shortcut relationship that holds between two entities based on their identity criteria"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002602",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "A shortcut relationship between two entities x and y1, such that the intent is that the relationship is functional and inverse function, but there is no guarantee that this property holds."
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002603",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "x is approximately equivalent to y if it is the case that x is equivalent, identical or near-equivalent to y"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002604",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty" ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112" : [ {
    "@value" : "'anterior end of organism' is-opposite-of 'posterior end of organism'"
  }, {
    "@value" : "'increase in temperature' is-opposite-of 'decrease in temperature'"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "x is the opposite of y if there exists some distance metric M, and there exists no z such as M(x,z) <= M(x,y) or M(y,z) <= M(y,x)."
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002605",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "x is indistinguishable from y if there exists some distance metric M, and there exists no z such as M(x,z) <= M(x,y) or M(y,z) <= M(y,x)."
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002606",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "c is a substance that treats d if c is a material entity (such as a small molecule or compound) and d is a pathological process, phenotype or disease, and c is capable of some activity that negative regulates or decreases the magnitude of d."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000118" : [ {
    "@value" : "treats"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ro/docs/causal-relations"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002607",
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "c is marker for d iff the presence or occurrence of d is correlated with the presence of occurrence of c, and the observation of c is used to infer the presence or occurrence of d. Note that this does not imply that c and d are in a direct causal relationship, as it may be the case that there is a third entity e that stands in a direct causal relationship with c and d."
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116" : [ {
    "@value" : "May be ceded to OBI"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002608",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty" ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115" : [ {
    "@value" : "Inverse of 'causal agent in process'"
  } ],
  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119" : [ {
