    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000013",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym" : [ {
    "@value" : "system element"
  } ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym" : [ {
    "@value" : "system variable"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Despite minor differences, SCO representation of systems and related architecture and composition is compatible with that of the System Core Ontology (Calhau et al., 2024). The system Core Ontology centers on socio-techno systems, primarily pointing to an intention/goal-directed representation of these systems. SCO representation, instead, adopts a more neutral modeling approach for complex systems, seeking to account for a wider range of systems. SCO is also more compact than the system Core Ontology. This is, however, adequate for the current purposes of SCO. \n\nWe envision employing the system Core Ontology as a starting point to extend SCO representation of system architecture, situations, properties, and functions. We also envision possible alignments and reciprocal implementations between these two ontologies.\n\nCalhau, R. F., Prince Sales, T., Oliveira, Í., Kokkula, S., Ferreira Pires, L., Cameron, D., Guizzardi, G., & Almeida, J. P. A. (2024). A System Core Ontology for Capability Emergence Modeling. In H. A. Proper, L. Pufahl, D. Karastoyanova, M. Van Sinderen, & J. Moreira (A c. Di), Enterprise Design, Operations, and Computing (Vol. 14367, pp. 3–20). Springer Nature Switzerland. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-46587-1_1\n\nUbbiali, G. A., Borghini, A., & Lange, M. C. (2024). Ontologies for Sustainability: Theoretical Challenges. https://doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/z8uqr"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "We envision discussions with subject matter experts regarding whether the current SCO representation of system-system component (and related environment) parthood is suitable or whether a proper parthood-based representation is more adequate. Insights for discussion may be found in Calhau et al. (2024) and Ubbiali et al. (2024).\n\nCalhau, R. F., Prince Sales, T., Oliveira, Í., Kokkula, S., Ferreira Pires, L., Cameron, D., Guizzardi, G., & Almeida, J. P. A. (2024). A System Core Ontology for Capability Emergence Modeling. In H. A. Proper, L. Pufahl, D. Karastoyanova, M. Van Sinderen, & J. Moreira (A c. Di), Enterprise Design, Operations, and Computing (Vol. 14367, pp. 3–20). Springer Nature Switzerland. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-46587-1_1\n\nUbbiali, G. A., Borghini, A., & Lange, M. C. (2024). Ontologies for Sustainability: Theoretical Challenges. https://doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/z8uqr"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "componente del sistema"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "composante de système"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "system component"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1437"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000014"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid1433"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A material entity that belongs to a system."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Un'entità materiale che appartiene a un sistema."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une entité matérielle qui appartient à un système."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000014",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym" : [ {
    "@value" : "system environment element"
  } ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym" : [ {
    "@value" : "system environment variable"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "We envision discussions with subject matter experts regarding whether the current SCO representation of system-system component (and related environment) parthood is suitable or whether a proper parthood-based representation is more adequate. Insights for discussion may be found in Calhau et al. (2024) and Ubbiali et al. (2024).\n\nCalhau, R. F., Prince Sales, T., Oliveira, Í., Kokkula, S., Ferreira Pires, L., Cameron, D., Guizzardi, G., & Almeida, J. P. A. (2024). A System Core Ontology for Capability Emergence Modeling. In H. A. Proper, L. Pufahl, D. Karastoyanova, M. Van Sinderen, & J. Moreira (A c. Di), Enterprise Design, Operations, and Computing (Vol. 14367, pp. 3–20). Springer Nature Switzerland. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-46587-1_1\n\nUbbiali, G. A., Borghini, A., & Lange, M. C. (2024). Ontologies for Sustainability: Theoretical Challenges. https://doi.org/10.31219/osf.io/z8uqr"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "componente dell' ambiente del systema"
  }, {
