  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000035",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "complex system indicator"
  } ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "system indicator"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "SCO indicator classes have been designed referring to the characterization of sustainable development indicators (SDGs indicators) proposed by SDGIO. we aimed to deepen this characterization and establish upper-level classes for SDGIO ones."
  }, {
    "@value" : "Due to the SCO focus on complex systems, indicator classes have been designed referring specifically to complex systems. Nevertheless, future implementations may broaden the space of application to also systems."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "indicateur"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "indicator"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "indicatore"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso" : [ {
    "@value" : "http://purl.unep.org/sdg/SDGIO_00000002"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000028"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1663"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1667"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid1659"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A complex system component with an indicator role."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Una componente del sistema complesso con un ruolo d’indicatore."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une composante de système complexe ayant un rôle d’indicateur."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000036",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym" : [ {
    "@value" : "complex system stakeholder, system stakeholder"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "parte interessata (stakeholder)"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "partie prenante (stakeholder)"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "stakeholder"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000028"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1675"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1679"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid1671"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A complex system component with a stakeholder role."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Una componente del sistema complesso con un ruolo di stakeholder."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une composante du système complexe avec un rôle de partie prenante."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000037",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Common Core Ontologies (CCO) provide corresponding properties for this and the “agent at time t” relations. See “see also” annotation”. As these relations apply specifically to the CCO “Agent” class and lack reference to time, the SCO creator decided to establish SCO's own versions of these relations, directly referring to the original source. See “adapted from” annotation."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "We envision revisions of the current SCO theory of agency. This is due to the limited power of explainability of present representation. A sounder and deeper interpretation of the causal role of an agent in an interaction, compared to other participants, is required.\n\nTentative proposal: a possible direction of implementation is towards a telic vision of agency intended as end-point driven. On this more fundamental neutral vision, a second layer of representation may be constructed to model intentionality, goals, and plans in relation to agency. Here, SCO may harmonize and align with UFO-C representation. \n\nFor insight for discussion see: \nGuarino, N., & Guizzardi, G. (2024). Processes as variable embodiments. Synthese, 203(4), 104. https://doi.org/10.1007/s11229-024-04505-2\nGuizzardi, G., de Almeida Falbo, R., & Guizzardi, R. (2008). Grounding software domain ontologies in the unified foundational ontology (UFO): The case of the ODE. Memorias de la XI Conferencia Iberoamericana de Software Engineering (CIbSE 2008), Recife, Pernambuco, Brasil, February 13-17, 2008, 127–140."
  }, {
    "@value" : "Future implementations may involve the introduction of an “act within the system” class, to deepen the characterization of system agency. Insights to implementation may come from the following CCO classes:\n\nhttp://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/Act \nhttp://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/IntentionalAct \nhttp://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/Agent \nhttp://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/AgentCapability \n\nThe aim is to align SCO and CCO “agent” classes in order to have a shared theory of agency."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "a un agent au temps t"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "ha un agente al tempo t"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "has agent at time t"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid149"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "comments to https://www.w3id.org/sco/sco-u#SCO_0000027 and https://www.w3id.org/sco/sco-u#SCO_0000029"
  }, {
    "@value" : "http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/agent_in \nhttp://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/has_agent"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000057"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000038"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A primitive relation between a process x, a continuant y, and a time at which y is causally active in x."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Una relazione primitiva tra un processo x, un continuante y e un tempo t a cui y è causalmente attivo in x."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une relation primitive entre un processus x, un continuant y et un temps t auquel y est causalement actif en x."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/adaptedFrom" : [ {
    "@value" : "https://doi.org/10.1186/gb-2005-6-5-r46"
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000038",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "We envision revisions of the current SCO theory of agency. This is due to the limited power of explainability of present representation. A sounder and deeper interpretation of the causal role of an agent in an interaction, compared to other participants, is required.\n\nTentative proposal: a possible direction of implementation is towards a telic vision of agency intended as end-point driven. On this more fundamental neutral vision, a second layer of representation may be constructed to model intentionality, goals, and plans in relation to agency. Here, SCO may harmonize and align with UFO-C representation. \n\nFor insight for discussion see: \nGuarino, N., & Guizzardi, G. (2024). Processes as variable embodiments. Synthese, 203(4), 104. https://doi.org/10.1007/s11229-024-04505-2\nGuizzardi, G., de Almeida Falbo, R., & Guizzardi, R. (2008). Grounding software domain ontologies in the unified foundational ontology (UFO): The case of the ODE. Memorias de la XI Conferencia Iberoamericana de Software Engineering (CIbSE 2008), Recife, Pernambuco, Brasil, February 13-17, 2008, 127–140."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid157"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "agent en au temps t"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "agent in at time t"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "agente in al tempo t"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#seeAlso" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "comments to https://www.w3id.org/sco/sco-u#SCO_0000027 and https://www.w3id.org/sco/sco-u#SCO_0000029"
  }, {
    "@value" : "See information under the inverse \"has agent at t\" property."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000056"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A primitive relation between a continuant x, a process y, and a time at which x is causally active in y."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Una relazione primitiva tra un continuante x, un processo y e un tempo t a cui x è causalmente attivo in y."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une relation primitive entre un continuant x, un processus y et un temps t auquel x est causalement actif en y."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@value" : "We envisage using this annotation property to highlight (indirectly)  the grounding of certain entities on perspectives and characterize them according to the embraced perspective(s).\n\nHere, it is provided an explicative example.\n\nLet’s consider that two users, A and B, endorse two different perspectives on sustainability, perspective A and perspective B. These perspectives lead to considering different complex system components as stakeholders of the complex system of interest. \n(This is an explicative example. It could also be the case that there is just one single user who wants to characterize the same entity according to two perspectives on sustainability, or who wants to provide an additional characterization according to a different perspective than the one previously covered.)\n\nWe suggest proceeding as follows. \nFirst, the class “perspective” can be instantiated with two “perspective” individuals, “perspective A” and “perspective B”. These “perspective” individuals will provide descriptions and other relevant information regarding users’ perspectives. Then, two subclasses, “stakeholder – A” and “stakeholder – B”, can be added to the class “stakeholder”. These classes could be created manually and further populated with further subclasses and/or individuals. Alternatively, they can be created by adding SPARQL query results to the ontology, directly as classes or as classes equivalent to some new classes manually created. Subclasses “stakeholder – A” and “stakeholder – B” will cover stakeholders according to the two different user perspectives. Finally, this annotation property can be used to annotate these two subclasses with the corresponding individual “perspective A” and “perspective B”. In proceeding as such, we can highlight the grounding of the role of stakeholder (entity) on perspective (entity) and provide stakeholder characterizations according to the two user perspectives. \n \nThis procedure supports establishing indirectly the grounding of certain entities on perspectives. This procedure, however, ensures the possibility to also account for different characterizations of the same entity according to different perspectives, thereby assisting in clarifying and comparing those perspectives.  Further, as a user may change perspective over time, this procedure can be performed whenever the perspective changes. New classes, covering time references, can be created and annotated with new perspectives. This will also assist in tracking users’ perspectives evolution over time. We contemplate the possible creation of an object property to directly model grounding on perspectives as part of future implementations of SCO."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "according to the perspective"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "secondo la prospettiva"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "selon la perspective"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#sco.owl/SCO_0000016"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000040",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "contenu informatif de la perspective de partie prenante (stakeholder)"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "contenuto informativo della prospettiva di parte interessata (stakeholder)"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "stakeholder perspective information content entity"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000004"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1687"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1691"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid1683"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A perspective information content entity of a stakeholder perspective."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Un contenu informatif de la perspective d’une perspective de partie prenante (stakeholder)."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Un contenuto informativo della prospettiva di una prospettiva di parte interessata (stakeholder)."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000041",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@value" : "Do not use this class directly. This class is constructed as a grouping for complex system properties, such as emergence and self-organization, in order to facilitate class retrieval and visualization."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "complex system property"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "proprietà del systema complesso"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000020"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "propriété de système complexe"
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000042",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A more extensive representation of emergence is required. A possible starting point may be the work of Calhau et al. (2024).\n\nCalhau, R. F., Prince Sales, T., Oliveira, Í., Kokkula, S., Ferreira Pires, L., Cameron, D., Guizzardi, G., & Almeida, J. P. A. (2024). A System Core Ontology for Capability Emergence Modeling. In H. A. Proper, L. Pufahl, D. Karastoyanova, M. Van Sinderen, & J. Moreira (A c. Di), Enterprise Design, Operations, and Computing (Vol. 14367, pp. 3–20). Springer Nature Switzerland. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-46587-1_1"
  }, {
    "@value" : "This class should be amended according to SCO implementations regarding system scales, levels, and change."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "emergence"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "emergenza (proprietà emergenti)"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "émergence (propriété émergentes"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000041"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1695"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#disjointWith" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000043"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A quality that inherits in a complex system by virtue of how the complex system behavior and properties at a macroscopic level are nontrivially envisaged from those at a more microscopic one."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Una qualità che il sistema complesso esibisce in virtù del fatto che il comportamento del sistema complesso e le sue proprietà a un livello macroscopico sono non-trivialmente predicibili da quelli a livello più microscopico."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une qualité qu’un système complexe exhibe en vertu du fait que le comportement du système complexe et ses propriétés à un niveau macroscopique sont non-trivialement prédictibles à partir de ceux aux niveaux plus microscopiques."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000043",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@value" : "This class should be amended according to SCO implementations regarding system scales, levels, and change."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "auto-organisation"
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "auto-organizzazione"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "self-organization"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000041"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid1699"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A quality that inherits in a complex system by virtue of how the complex system components spontaneously arrange, globally generating macroscopic and microscopic structures and behaviors, without any internal and/or external controls."
  }, {
    "@language" : "it",
    "@value" : "Una qualità che il sistema complesso esibisce in virtù del fatto che le componenti del sistema complesso si organizzino spontaneamente, generando globalmente strutture e comportamenti macroscopici e microscopici, senza alcun controllo interno e/o esterno."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Une qualité qu’un système complexe exhibe en vertu du fait que les composantes du système complexe s’organisent spontanément, générant globalement des structures et comportements macroscopiques et microscopiques, sans aucun contrôle interne et/ou externe."
  } ],
  "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional"
  } ]
} ]